United Democratic Alliance has announced that its nominations in ten constituencies have been suspended following constituencies; Mt Elgon, Malava, Likuyani, and Lugari owing to logistical challenges; to Saturday, April 16, 2022. Turkana East, Turkana Central, and Bumula, similarly due to logistical challenges, to Tuesday the 19 of April 2022. "Nandi Hills, where we sadly lost one of the aspirants through a tragic road accident, to Tuesday the 19th of April 2022. The party leadership continues to condole with the family," UDA NEB chairperson Anthony Mwaura said. However, the nominations for the governor, senator, woman rep and ward level in Nandi Hills are ongoing. Nakuru Town West Constituency nominations will also be held on Tuesday the 19th of April 2022. But nominations for Senate, Woman Representative, and ward level are ongoing. Finally, nominations in the Narok South constituency have been postponed to Tuesday, April 19, 2022.